bereits von einem zweigeteilten Baskenland gesprochen werden muss. Auf Basis des Verhältnisses von Sprache und Identität im Baskenland wird ein eigenes Modell zur Untersuchung und Beschreibung von Identität entwickelt.  aThis work undertakes an empirical analysis of current linguistic circumstances in the Basque Country. The two Basque subpopulations living on French and Spanish territory are compared and contrasted in terms of various parameters, including the prevalence of Basque cultural traditions and language, and related attitudes about Basque identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aBasque languagexVariation. 0aLanguages in contactxPaís Vasco (Spain) 0aLanguages in contactxPaís Vasco (Spain). 0aLanguages in contactxPays Basque (France) 0aLanguages in contactxPays Basque (France). 0aLanguages in contactxPaís Vasco (Spain). 4aSprache und Identität. 4aSprachkontaktforschung. 4aSprachvariation. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh  aLanguage and Identity.  aLinguistic Contact Phenomena.  aLinguistic Variation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103933090 cprintz978311037239740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036687740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110366877423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110366877/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014